detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value:
Introduction to Danish language and culture at a beginners level. Get to know Danish in a low-stress environment where you develop your language skills step by step. No traditional, high-stakes tests or exams. Focus is on spoken language, practical use and conversation through dialog practices, short presentations and in-class exercises. Cultural topics include: Areas in Denmark, Hygge, the Danes odd relationship with their flag, the Danish monarchy and Christmas in Denmark .

Book: Puls 1, Chapters 1-3

Interested in other courses within the Department of Central, Eastern and Northern European Studies? 
Click here.

detailResultFields.value:
This course is part of the Coordinated Arts Program, Political Science, Philosophy and  Economics stream, https://cap.arts.ubc.ca/streams/political-science-philosophy-economics-ppe/. Students must register in both Term 1 and Term 2 courses in CAP.

Follow the prompts to register in all stream seminars (1), lectures (2), and tutorials (1-2)
each term.

For step-by-step instructions, please visit: https://cap.arts.ubc.ca/program/registration/


If you encounter any issues with registration into CAP, please contact us at support.fyip@ubc.ca
